      "content": "If a business encroaches on neighbor's lots, the city typically starts with a formal notice of violation from the Planning or Code Enforcement department. These violations are usually managed through a compliance process, requiring the business owner to remedy the encroachment within a specified timeframe. If they fail to comply, the city has the authority to impose fines or, in persistent cases, seek a court injunction to force removal. Ultimately, the City of Portland uses these official channels to enforce property lines and zoning rules.",
